# Merge conflicts

When resolving Git merge conflicts in this project, **always keep the `HEAD` version** (the code between `<<<<<<< HEAD` and `=======`). Remove conflict markers and delete the incoming block (between `=======` and `>>>>>>> ...`).

If both sides contain unique useful changes, still prefer HEAD unless the user explicitly asks to merge both.
